# IPFS Javascript Relay Node
This is an example of an IPFS Relay Node. The code in this repo is used for the talk "Building a Decentrazlied Twitter with IPFS". 

## Installion/Usage
You will need to have Node installed. To run the server, type `node server.js` in the terminal. 

### Cloud Installation

**Login to Heroku**
$ heroku login
**Login to the Container Registry**
$ heroku container:login
**Clone the repo**
$ git clone https://github.com/ShariqT/ipfs-js-server-node.git
$ cd ipfs-js-server-node
**Create a Heroku app**
$ heroku create
**Build and push the image**
$ heroku container:push web
**Release the image to your app**
$ heroku container:release web
# Scale to one free worker
$ heroku ps:scale web=1
**Open the app in the browser**
$ heroku open